        <briefdescription>
<para>Serializes the specified input data to a save file to be loaded later. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Uses binary serialization to write the transformed data to disk. If a file with the specified name already exists, it will be overwritten</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="templateparam"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>TData</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The type of the data to be serialized. Must implement <ref refid="interface_unity_utils_1_1_script_utils_1_1_save_system_1_1_i_save_data" kindref="compound">ISaveData</ref></para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>TInput</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The type of the input data to be transformed and saved.</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>inputData</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The input data to be transformed and saved to the file.</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>fileName</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The name of the file to which the data will be saved. Do not include any file extensions, file extension is determined by <ref refid="class_unity_utils_1_1_script_utils_1_1_save_system_1_1_save_system_config" kindref="compound">SaveSystemConfig</ref></para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>createSaveData</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>A function that transforms the input data into a serializable object of type <emphasis>TData</emphasis> </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
</para>
